The paper deals with autonomous flight of drones in dynamic environments, which involves challenges in robotics such as state estimation, perception, and action under resource constraints. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses a convolutional neural network (CNN) for vision-based navigation, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of a CNN also implies that the paper could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with control and planning of autonomous systems, which suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
